# 1Password env-file for `op run` — resolves PACKAGES_READ_TOKEN from 1Password
# at install time so the value never has to live in shell env.
#
# Usage:
#   op run --env-file=.env.op -- npm install
#   op run --env-file=.env.op -- npm ci
#
# Why: PACKAGES_READ_TOKEN (a GitHub PAT with read:packages scope) authenticates
# `@brikdesigns/*` package pulls from GitHub Packages via .npmrc substitution.
# Previously sourced from ~/.zshenv → ~/.secrets/brik-packages.env, leaving it
# exposed to any `env | grep`-style command from an agent or shell session
# (brik-llm#593 — 2026-05-22 PAT leak). Resolving via op-run keeps the value
# in 1Password until the moment npm spawns and drops it after the child exits.
#
# 1P item purpose: `packages-read` (brik-llm/operations/security/secrets.yaml).
# CI is unaffected — GH Actions and Netlify supply PACKAGES_READ_TOKEN directly
# as repo/site env; `op run` is a developer-machine concern only.
#
# Tracking: brikdesigns#253 (this repo), brik-llm#570 (cross-repo audit).

PACKAGES_READ_TOKEN=op://Development/lgpwdjwwdndjneddgjqafeb4eq/credential
